      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5a89bf12-1c56-42ec-92b1-7491fe16dad7",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Pixels of Me Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students use the first box in their Planning Guide to brainstorm hobbies or interests they have and any careers that might be associated with them. Allow students to share their lists, idea webs, or sketches with an elbow partner as this may give them more ideas that they had not thought of themselves.  ",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Warm Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Encourage students to come up with some hobbies they have both in and outside of school. The more they come up with, the more ideas they will have to choose from for their project pixel design. You can also prompt students to think about how their interests relate to their future career goals."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5a89bf12-1c56-42ec-92b1-7491fe16dad7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed8aeb5d-7d80-4c83-90f1-d0c4f99a46c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4679481e-c4af-4b66-8902-735d67a53173",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4679481e-c4af-4b66-8902-735d67a53173",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed8aeb5d-7d80-4c83-90f1-d0c4f99a46c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "722672fb-dec0-480a-8edc-7adc7bba13c3",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students use the second box in their Planning Guide to brainstorm ideas for how they could represent any their ideas or interests visually. Again, allow students to share their ideas with a partner as this might give them more ideas beyond than what they had thought of themselves.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What skills have you learned in this unit that could help you create this pixel image?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students should be able to explain how they can use the Neighborhood grid, Painter object and Python code such as functions, loops, and conditionals to “paint” their image. They should also explain how they can use computational thinking skills (decomposition, pattern recognition, abstraction, and algorithms) as well as skills and characteristics such as creativity, problem-solving, team work, detail-oriented, and others discussed throughout the unit to create their algorithms.  "
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "722672fb-dec0-480a-8edc-7adc7bba13c3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed8aeb5d-7d80-4c83-90f1-d0c4f99a46c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "abc03c74-3550-4dde-b29f-664d4e99615c",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the first part of the project requirements.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the remaining project requirements.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to read the rubric on the last two pages of the project planning guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What do you notice about the project requirements and rubric? What does success look like for this project?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students share what they notice about the project requirements and rubric and identify the components to implement in their program.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What barriers do you anticipate to achieving success on this project?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students identify barriers they anticipate and share any questions they have about the project.",
        "duration": "30",
        "name": "Activity",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "abc03c74-3550-4dde-b29f-664d4e99615c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed8aeb5d-7d80-4c83-90f1-d0c4f99a46c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b96aae5f-a992-4377-b78d-3028f5e77433",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b96aae5f-a992-4377-b78d-3028f5e77433",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed8aeb5d-7d80-4c83-90f1-d0c4f99a46c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3782699a-3f8b-430a-81b2-0ff75904407c",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the tasks students should complete on Day 1 to complete the project:\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the tasks students should complete on Day 2 to complete the project:\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the tasks students should complete on Day 3 to complete the project:\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Inform students that they will have the AI Chatbot on Level 2 to use for whatever support they need throughout the process. They can use AI to help them brainstorm, decompose their image, write pseudocode, or help debug any errors.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to sketch their pixels of me design, identify the repeated patterns in the image, the functions they should define to create those patterns, and write pseudocode for their functions to plan their project on the Pixels of Me Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Help students who might be struggling with any of the decomposition steps or with writing their pseudocode for their functions. Encourage students to use the AI chatbot if they need help getting started.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Emphasize that the Pixels of Me design should be simple enough to create in the given timeframe while being complex enough to utilize the methods, user-defined functions with loops and conditionals. Students can use the AI chatbot to help them brainstorm different ideas for images they might use to represent their interests."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3782699a-3f8b-430a-81b2-0ff75904407c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed8aeb5d-7d80-4c83-90f1-d0c4f99a46c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3e03f445-09d2-49c9-a073-7b4184a67184",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3e03f445-09d2-49c9-a073-7b4184a67184",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed8aeb5d-7d80-4c83-90f1-d0c4f99a46c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "65857446-066d-4004-bd7d-c0c09c2f86df",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 13, Level 1 to select the corresponding grid size that they selected in their project planning guide.",
        "progression_name": "Pixels of Me Project"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "65857446-066d-4004-bd7d-c0c09c2f86df",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed8aeb5d-7d80-4c83-90f1-d0c4f99a46c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f0bc93f6-7358-4633-83fc-eaf7f581f6f3",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Ensure students are on task. Encourage students to share and discuss their functions with a thought partner while working. As you move around the room, engage students with questions about their image, its repeated parts, the functions they plan on creating, and how they might use the AI chatbot."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
