      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4df17556-f478-47e6-9829-8a8fbcebe8ce",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to complete the Day 1 Reflection section in their project planning guide. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Ensure students are discussing and sharing these reflection questions with a thought partner. ",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor and with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4df17556-f478-47e6-9829-8a8fbcebe8ce",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ed8aeb5d-7d80-4c83-90f1-d0c4f99a46c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1597fa14-bfcb-4522-a6c1-d5c69cd5f054",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Which function did you write first? Why?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students should be able to explain why they chose to start with writing the function they did. Perhaps they chose to start with that function because it was the quickest to test. Or perhaps they knew that it would hit the most rows in the rubric by utilizing various algorithmic concepts and organized code.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Warm Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Keep this warm up quick and short in order to give students as much time as possible to program their image today."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1597fa14-bfcb-4522-a6c1-d5c69cd5f054",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a11bb807-22fd-4857-af50-5c0370612683"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6ffafa57-8bda-4060-980a-d7ab2388cab1",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6ffafa57-8bda-4060-980a-d7ab2388cab1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a11bb807-22fd-4857-af50-5c0370612683"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e39f0638-6ae2-4e95-8d13-ae106ff9e258",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the tasks to complete for Day 2 of the project.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 13, Level 1 to continue developing their projects.",
        "duration": "35",
        "name": "Activity"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e39f0638-6ae2-4e95-8d13-ae106ff9e258",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a11bb807-22fd-4857-af50-5c0370612683"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7befe06d-dca2-4ff8-bc2f-ec1fc82b86d4",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Ensure students are on task. Remind students to comment their code with meaningful descriptions. As you move around the room, encourage students to test their functions incrementally (e.g., one function at a time). \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to TAG one to two peers' programs. As they have done previously, students will leave this TAG feedback on sticky notes at their peer’s computer. ",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Students may be at different points when it is time for the TAG review. Emphasize to students that their work does not need to be completed to get feedback. Remind students that the problem-solving and development process is iterative and that receiving feedback from peers while they are working can help give them additional insights, perspectives, and guidance."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7befe06d-dca2-4ff8-bc2f-ec1fc82b86d4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a11bb807-22fd-4857-af50-5c0370612683"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bd4576b6-bf4f-47ef-98a2-4a23feaa0d92",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bd4576b6-bf4f-47ef-98a2-4a23feaa0d92",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a11bb807-22fd-4857-af50-5c0370612683"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "db48dc4e-6b62-4401-bc44-423ce7999d6b",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to complete the Day 2 Reflection section in their project planning guide. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Ensure students are discussing and sharing these reflection questions with a thought partner. ",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor and with the class."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "You can use the Day 2 Reflection as evidence for Reflection on AI and Peer Feedback rubric criteria."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "db48dc4e-6b62-4401-bc44-423ce7999d6b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a11bb807-22fd-4857-af50-5c0370612683"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "abe18c88-6960-4bb6-aed0-319b9149826a",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "abe18c88-6960-4bb6-aed0-319b9149826a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a11bb807-22fd-4857-af50-5c0370612683"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d9895f1d-54fb-42c9-b31d-b95939b3e9a6",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the discussion prompts.\n- *What are you most proud of about your project so far?*\n- *What challenges do you still need to overcome before submitting your project?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students share what they are proud of about their project and any challenges they still need to overcome before they submit their project. ",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Warm Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, allow students to share with several people so they can share what they are proud of while hearing about other’s challenges to help them feel okay about their own challenges."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d9895f1d-54fb-42c9-b31d-b95939b3e9a6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4c3c7c5d-70df-4c94-904d-34751f9ff571"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "154810d3-41bb-4296-b717-682523b4d04f",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "154810d3-41bb-4296-b717-682523b4d04f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4c3c7c5d-70df-4c94-904d-34751f9ff571"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "cb25743a-6c5f-4ad9-a403-432350cd7d80",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the tasks to complete for Day 3 of the project.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students self-assess their project using the rubric on the Pixels of Me Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Level 1 to finish developing their Pixels of Me projects.",
        "duration": "30",
        "name": "Activity"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "cb25743a-6c5f-4ad9-a403-432350cd7d80",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4c3c7c5d-70df-4c94-904d-34751f9ff571"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "72629568-453d-4edf-9c99-8cabf55ee9f8",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Instruct students to use the feedback they received from their TAG review and self-assessment to finalize their Pixels of Me project. Have students submit their projects at the end of the allotted time.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Ensure students are on task. Remind students to comment their code with meaningful descriptions. Have students review their rubric and prioritize work on any rows where they do not yet show extensive evidence.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Distribute several sticky notes to each student for the gallery walk.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to participate in the Gallery Walk by displaying their project and then going around the room to view classmate’s projects and leave sticky notes with kudos, questions or observations.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Move around the room to observe how students are engaging with the displayed projects. Encourage students to leave a note about what they find interesting or insightful about their peers' work. Prompt them to consider how the pixel images represent their classmates’ identities. Ensure that students are thoughtfully engaging with a variety of projects, not just those of their closest peers."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "72629568-453d-4edf-9c99-8cabf55ee9f8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4c3c7c5d-70df-4c94-904d-34751f9ff571"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "872ace58-70fe-43bb-a38c-acdc1ba79875",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to complete the End of Project Reflection section in their project planning guide. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Ensure students are discussing and sharing these reflection questions with a thought partner. ",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor and with the class."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "You can use the Pixels of Me Planning Guide as evidence for the Computational Thinking in Planning rubric criteria. The End of Project Reflection as evidence for Reflection on AI and Peer Feedback rubric criteria."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "872ace58-70fe-43bb-a38c-acdc1ba79875",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4c3c7c5d-70df-4c94-904d-34751f9ff571"
      }
    },
